  "prompt": "What is voltage regulation formula?",
  "response": "Voltage regulation is a measure of how much the voltage changes from no load to full load on a system, and it is expressed as a percentage. The formula for voltage regulation is:\n\n\\[\n\\text{Voltage Regulation (\\%)} = \\frac{V_{NL} - V_{FL}}{V_{FL}} \\times 100\n\\]\n\nWhere:\n- \\( V_{NL} \\) = No-load voltage (the voltage at the output terminal when no load is connected)\n- \\( V_{FL} \\) = Full-load voltage (the voltage at the output terminal when the maximum load is connected)\n\nA lower percentage indicates better voltage regulation, meaning the voltage remains more stable under varying load conditions.",
